In a speech delivered in Detroit, President Biden celebrated the passage of the infrastructure bill and discussed its impact on various aspects of the American economy. He mentioned that leading rating agencies have confirmed that the bill will not add to inflationary pressures. He also highlighted the strong job growth in the country and the positive impact of the bill on wages. The President praised General Motors (GM) for its leadership in the electric vehicle industry and its commitment to transitioning to electric vehicles by 2035. He emphasized the importance of American leadership in electric vehicles and announced plans to install a national network of charging stations. The President also discussed the broader implications of the infrastructure bill, including investment in clean energy, improvements to roads and bridges, expansion of broadband access, and addressing climate change. He emphasized that the bill is fully paid for and will not increase the deficit. The President concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the American people and their ability to compete in the 21st century.